genresAdvancedInfo.name: concertina
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Concertina is a type of small, free-reed instrument that resembles an accordion. It is commonly used in traditional folk music, particularly in Ireland and England. The concertina is played by pressing the buttons on either side of the instrument, which opens and closes the bellows and produces sound. It is known for its bright, distinctive sound and is often used for solo performances or in small ensembles.
